To complete this tutorial, you will need a GitHub account. Make sure you have an internet connection too!

Set up an account on GitHub

1. Open GitHub website by clicking on the given link: https://github.com/ 
2. Click on Sign up button on the upper right corner of the homepage.
3. Fill your valid credentials and solve the puzzle (will not be too hard :P) and click on Create an account
4. GitHub provides Student Developer Pack to students which allows you to create private repositories. You can also continue with the Free plan. We are moving forward with the free plan.
5. You are all set to use the platform. Go back to the homepage (https://github.com/) and log into your account.
